Module-4*Recognizing_Abnormal_or_Malicious_traffic_01

Troubleshooting the Network

Describe the issue
Gather the information and narrow the scope
Consider what could have caused the problem
Outline a plan to solve the problem
Implement the plan
Test the implementation
Document the results and repeat if not resolved



Prepare for Failure

Have a physical and logical map of the network
Have a list of all protocols used on the network
Know how the traffic is switched and routed
Describe all the points of contact from internal to external network
Have an established baseline


Baseline

Plan
Capture
Analyze
Save


Describe the issue: Gather information on what happened and where it happened to narrow down the scope of the problem.
Plan and implement: Outline a plan to solve the problem, involve your team, and document everything before making changes.
Prepare for failure: Have a physical and logical map of the network, list all protocols, and establish a baseline to compare against when troubleshooting.






